Class Node

java.lang.Object
  fr.michaelm.jump.plugin.topology.Node
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable
public class Node
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable

A Node is a Coordinate located "on" or "near" a LinearComponent and holding a reference to a segment of this LinearComponent.

Node

public Node(LinearComponent component,
            int segmentIndex,
            com.vividsolutions.jts.geom.Coordinate coordinate)
Creates a new Node located on or in front of segment with index segmetIndex.

Parameters:
component - the linear component this node is related to
segmentIndex - index of the segment this node is projected to
coordinate - the coordinate of the original node (before any projection)

Node

public Node(LinearComponent component,
            int segmentIndex,
            com.vividsolutions.jts.geom.Coordinate coordinate,
            double snapTolerance)
Creates a new Node located on or in front of segment with index segmetIndex.

Parameters:
component - the linear component this node is related to
segmentIndex - index of the segment this node is projected to
coordinate - the coordinate of the original node (before any projection)
snapTolerance - defines how the node will be projected onto the segment (if distance from node to the target segment ends is lesser than snap tolerance, the node will be projected on the nearest of these ends)

getProjection

public com.vividsolutions.jts.geom.Coordinate getProjection()
Get the projection of the Node to its LinearComponent. The projection can be either a perpendicular projection or a projection to the nearest node if a non null tolerance is defined for this Node. Projection is computed only once.
